(Translated by Google) In summary the restaurant is good. They take good care of you and are friendly. The margaritas are recommended and their burritos have nothing to envy anywhere else. The coffee is served in a very nice little jug but the taste of the coffee can improve.  The Burning Saturday club has a lot to improve. They do not have fixed prices and sometimes it occurs to them to charge less if you arrive early and sometimes not. There are people who arrive early and may be eating and drinking making more money on that than on the cost of entry. The music is terrible, really bad and the shows are very long and boring. - There is room for improvement. The music should be current and not just bachata and cumbia, but music that appealed to everyone. Shows should be better planned and directed, perhaps even themed and supervised or better yet, shorter.  (Original) En resumen el restaurante es bueno. Te atienden bien y son amables. Las margaritas son recomendables y sus burritos no tienen nada que envidiar a cualquier otro lugar. El café lo sirven en una Jarrita muy bonita pero el sabor del café puede mejorar.  El club de los sábados Ardiente tiene mucho que mejorar. No tienen precios fijos y a veces se les ocurre cobrar menos si llegas temprano y a veces no. Hay gente que llega temprano y puede estar comiendo y tomando haciéndole más dinero en eso que en el costo de entrada. La música es terrible, realmente mala y los shows son muy largos y aburridos. — Hay campo para mejorar. La música debería ser actual y no solo bachata y cumbia, sino música que apelé a todos. Los shows deberían ser mejor planeados y con mejor dirección, quizás incluso con temática y supervisión o mejor aún, más cortos.
The lady that works there is rude and gives terrible service.

The restaurant is good but their club “Ardiente” on Saturdays is terrible. They charge $10 cover, drinks are overpriced, drag shows are honestly the worst in DC and sometimes they don’t even have drag queens but the girl promoters doing a random dance. When they have shows, they are way too long and boring. They don’t allow you to go out briefly, if let’s say you need to go to your car (they will charge you again!). And the Cherry on top is that the music is terrible, the DJ doesn’t even know how to sync the songs well. The only good thing is the people, they are friendly and they have a basement area where the restaurant is open during their party, so you can escape the horrors of the “drag” show, or bad music.

Was really hoping this neighborhood spot would be good. I have tried the Mount Pleasant location which was good, but after being in Brightwood almost 15 years, it was my first time in this location. It was not family friendly environment with a bar full of profane drunks. The staff was friendly enough but appeared oblivious to the inappropriateness of their sauced patrons until verbally sparring with them. If the food have been great then my elementary school kids dropping an F bomb would have been worth it. Unfortunately all three meals were subpar. Hopefully management can turn this place back into a restaurant.
